standing how the Google search algorithms  work -  we build the  marketing strategy for promotion individually for each project, and this strategy always leads to a positive result.<a href=\"http://rightonit1/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/seo-slide-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1266\" src=\"http://rightonit1/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/seo-slide-1-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"seo-slide-1\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a> </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Selecting keywords for SEO</b></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Analyzing the group of goods in the search engines</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Selecting keyword queries</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Website Analyzing </b></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Searching for errors in the page\'s code</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Detecting errors in the website structure </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Analyzing the content</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Counting inbound links</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Optimizing the website</b></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Correcting the structure of the website (menu, layouts and etc)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Patching bugs in the source code</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 40