 need to frequently (eg weekly) to change the keywords, then contextual advertising gives you this possibility, the achievement of <strong><a href=\"http://rightonit1/\">SEO</a></strong> results in the promotion of new keyword phrases will take much more time;\r\nThe need to always be on the first query page - Ads give you stable results, which allows you to always be “first”, but it depends on changes in rates or a lack of money in the account, you can fall out of the visible area;\r\nYour budget - to promote a whole lot more favorable to other types of advertising (and on the Internet, and on radio and television), moreover, provides a steady flow of visitors, contextual advertising, especially in the popular topics can be very expensive.\r\n\r\nYou can combine both methods <a href=\"http://rightonit1/seo-and-organic-search-ranking/\">SEO</a> and paid Ads , it will increase visits in the short term to your target audience.\r\nThe more visits you have , the more customers you have !','Paid Ads vs  SEO','','publish','closed','closed','','paid-ads-vs-seo','','','2025-10-20 10:47:28','2025-10-20 07:47:28','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/paid-ads-vs-seo/',0,'post','',0),(1770,3,'2016-12-31 06:26:07','2016-12-31 06:26:07','<h2>SEO why is so important?</h2>\r\nDo you want people to find your website through organic web search?\r\n\r\n... Of course You do... Everyone does want to be in TOP10 Google Organic Search...\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Keyword Research</strong> – Figure out the \"low competitive\" words, highly searched terms in your field of business.  Find out exactly what your clients are looking for.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Analyse your website </strong> – Is it done the right way for proper optimization?  Well... If Your website was developed in Our company - you can skip this step - because the answer is YES. Your website is definitely designed and built RIGHT way and already have <a href=\"http://rightonit1/seo-san-diego/\">basic SEO</a>, Always!</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Who are your\'s main competitors? - </strong> What positions do they have  - what keywords they use?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Backlink Building</strong> – It’s very important to build strong supporting network</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>SMM</strong> -  Google+, Facebook, Instagram, Yelp and other accounts</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Report and Analyze</strong> - positions, backlinks, traffic and conversion.</li>\r\n</ul>','SEO why is so important?','','publish','closed','closed','','seo-why-is-so-important','','','2025-10-20 10:47:07','2025-10-20 07:47:07','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/seo-why-is-so-important/',0,'post','',0),(1771,3,'2016-12-31 06:26:07','2016-12-31 06:26:07','<h2>Marketing Optimization</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The list of approaches used by the optimizer: </span>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Marketing optimization  В2В</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this case marketing is aimed at searching new commercial partners in the business environment. We should warn from the beginning that it is a hard task, since it does not permit subjective representation of the company and its products. This means products and services for business should be represented only from practical point of view. This should be taken into account when drafting text content and distributing links in it.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Marketing optimization  В2С</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This task is easier, but at the same time it is connected with substantial share of creativity and requires innovative approach. The company’s products in this case are offered to an average customer who chooses products and services not as a professional, but as an amateur. This means that bare digits are for such amateur are boring and uninformative. You need a catchy text and rich illustrations. </span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The goal of the modern commercial website design  is selling services or products. This goal is the main and all online <a href=\"https://web-designservice.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/elements-of-optimization-wheel.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-1245\" src=\"https://web-designservice.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/elements-of-optimization-wheel-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"elements-of-optimization-wheel\" width=\"255\" height=\"255\" /></a>marketing capacities are used to reach this particular goal. Being in the TOP is more important for optimization in B2C scheme. The website targeted at sales to individuals should have higher position (in top three) in search results, bright design and convenient software to make quick purchases “here and now”.  The situation with B2B marketing is slightly different. In this case design heads for back and text content becomes first. Search marketing also looses its positions, because “specialized” websites are rarely created for occasional sales. The </span><b><a href=\"http://rightonit1/\">website marketing</a></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> heads back, but does not loose its positions. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For example, the main specific of the search optimization for a multipage website of a furniture factory or a metalworks plant is technical specialization where it is more complicated to distribute keywords. In addition, the text should be written for people who visited the website for purpose, and, probably, already have a range of similar offers. Since the sales in this business niche are connected with large amounts of money the competition will be tough. And the first impression from your website will have the major impact on the decision of the potential client. The main difference of the websites marketed in B2B sector is plenty of texts giving full answers on any questions that an average client may have. If the websites targeted at clients that are individuals use graphics as their main weapon, then the websites targeted at companies focus on texts. They should be optimized very carefully avoiding excessive extravagance that may frighten a conservative client. The websites for companies are easier in programming. Usually, it is not needed at all. Purchasing expensive equipment or ordering services from a big enterprise requires long negotiations and collective decision making. That is why no one is hurrying a potential client who represents a company, but at the same time online marketing is made is such a way that the website be easy to find using certain search requests. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Loads of technical terms in the description of the product offered by the company is an important feature of search marketing. There are a lot of such requests, because the offered products and services usually cannot be described briefly and a potential client enters in the search field various words that are more or less associated the item that he is searching for. The more complicated the product offered by the company is, the wider will be the list of keywords from which the semantic kernel of the website will be formed. The psychology of the websites occupying B2C sector is aimed at motivating for immediate purchase. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Comparatively low price of a product or a service, and usability of purchase making are the additional motivation for a visitor. Since a majority of text content on such websites is replaced by graphics the search optimization may be slightly complicated. From other point the search optimization for B2C sector is free from technical terms which significantly facilitate work of optimizer. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Additional convenience when working with B2C websites is the fact that they are usually marketed using famous brand names that gives to the optimizer many opportunities in search marketing, especially if one or another brand appearing on the pages is the its highest popularity points and ensures permanently high demand. Even taking into account high competition among similar websites the marketing will go clock-work! It is more difficult to market special equipment and services without high demand in everyday life, for these reasons the optimizer tries to keep every request. That is why we need the extensive list of keywords mentioned above. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In any case working with both ways of search optimization requires excellent knowledge of search algorithms of the search and indexation of websites by search engines, and not only national search engines, but also foreign ones.</span>\r\n\r\nFill out the form below and we will help you with your Marketing Optimisation\r\n\r\n[caldera_form id=\"CF5591c458259a5\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Marketing Optimization','','publish','closed','closed','','marketing-opimisation','','','2025-10-20 10:46:27','2025-10-20 07:46:27','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/marketing-opimisation/',0,'post','',0),(1773,3,'2016-12-31 06:26:07','2016-12-31 06:26:07','<h2>Website marketing SEO for low frequency queries</h2>\r\nIt is assumed that the main goal of search engine optimisation (SEO) is when the website reaches the first page of organic search .\r\n\r\nOn the one hand it is a significant achievement, because nowadays in the era of the Developed Internet it becomes more and more difficult to market the website to the TOP, on the other hand the marketing goal should not be narrowed to primitive rise of the website. As a matter of fact the main task for every website owner is to attract <a href=\"https://web-designservice.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/keyphrase-search-frequency.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1251\" src=\"https://web-designservice.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/keyphrase-search-frequency-300x188.png\" alt=\"keyphrase-search-frequency\" width=\"300\" height=\"188\" /></a>visitors.\r\nThe time when you could seduce the visitor tricking him or playing on small passions has passed. Nowadays the other tactics are actual: to make the user visit the website you need to interest him in the content of the marketed resource. As the practice showed, people very reluctantly visit the website under which link is just an unclear cutting from keywords is located. It means that when building a semantic kernel from the most popular requests you should not forget about readability of the text, after all even if the first page of search result will be filled with the most relevant (according to a search engine), but absolutely useless (from the point of view of their information value) websites, the disappointed user will go to the second page, and then and to the third. As a result value of a well-known and desired by many high rankings will decrease repeatedly and nobody will win.\r\nIt turns out that the contents of the web page drafted only for people none the worse means for marketing than the semantic kernel counted by optimizers specifically for the search engine. Or maybe even more, after all, the user can always go to the second page where he will find what he was looking for.\r\n<h2>User-friendly SEO</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://rightonit1/la-mesa-seo-help-la-mesa-search-engine-optimization/\">Website SEO</a>  \"for people\" gives a considerably better result, especially, if it is carried out under different requests which will be most interesting for potential visitors of this resource. Thus, some requests can be combined on the page, this will allow attracting a wide group of visitors. Only, as always, you should not forget about useful contents. If you are aiming to cover as much audience as possible then provide it with interesting and relevant content which will be able not only to entice, but also to hold the audience.\r\nIn this regard, low-frequency requests gain importance. These requests are not used very actively by many optimizers as they require good knowledge of the target segment of network and careful calculations. It is easy to miss with low-frequency requests and receive no expected visitors, but if the optimizer manages to select proper requests and unite them with the text, then the <strong>web marketing</strong> will bring an excellent result in the form of the interested visitors who, usually, easily turn into clients!\r\n<h3>The advantages of low frequency queries <a href=\"http://rightonit1/\">SEO San Diego</a> are listed below:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Small competition.</strong>\r\nIt is very unlikely that someone will market his own website using the requests that you have chosen, this is why your website will quicker get to the top of search results.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attracting only interested visitors.</strong>\r\nIf a user types a certain phrase, this means that the possibility of him making an order when visiting your website increases significantly.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Prolonged effect of <em>internet marketing.</em></strong>\r\nSince the competition is considerably lower the website will be in the TOP significantly longer. In addition, website <strong>SEO</strong> using low-frequency requests will allow using several keyword phrases on one page without risk of the page being too long.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Characterized by higher accuracy.</strong>\r\nSuch requests consist of several words and allow offering to the visitor the particular product or service for which the visitor is searching. For example, with “coach” request the visitor will get to the root catalogue and will be searching for the needed product, but the at the same time the request “red leather coach” will get him to the needed page in a few seconds.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>No need to frequently repeat the request on the page.</strong>\r\nSince the request is highly accurate there is no need to repeat in many times in the text. Consequently the text becomes more reada