 your website. For instance, if you post video on YouTube, the link will connect people with YouTube, and it won’t increase the popularity of your own website. However, while posting videos on YouTube you can also put a link of the original source of the video in comments or description and it will be useful for promoting your website in all cases.\r\n\r\nIf your aim is not solely restricted to gaining links but you also want the audience to be informed of the content and spread it, you must post your video content on one of the popular video hosting like YouTube, Flickr, Vimeo, Ustream, Wistia, Vidyard, etc. Those video hosting usually have many visitors and will help you to attract the target audience.\r\n\r\nWhile choosing the video hosting for posting videos you must consider several facts and your choice will depend on the fact if there are any restrictions connected with posting videos. For instance the beginners may post on YouTube videos with duration less than or15 minutes. To increase the time limit you have to pass account verification via phone number.\r\n\r\nThe other important criterion of choosing video hosting, are the tools available for video’s search optimization, as it will help you to have a good ranking in search systems. Particularly pay attention to the thematic description of the posted video content and the possibility of using tags and links to your web source.\r\n\r\nSometimes the website owners use doubling to spread widely their videos. It means that they post video twice: once on their own website and then on video hosting. But, from the point of view of promotion it proves inefficient as all the video links will connect the audience with the video hosting.\r\n\r\nVideo content is a powerful source of attracting the attention of the audience to your website. If you use it correctly it will increase the efficiency of promoting website. For professional advice you’d better turn to special web-studio for web-design.\r\n<h3 data-fontsize=\