n order to define your future competitors pay attention to the search results while using certain key-words. Place the important thematic inquiry into the search-line and view the first ten results. Though the results may differ depending on the used key-words, still, there will be websites which usually appear among first results. Those websites are your real rivals.\r\n\r\nThe given method of defining the competitors based on the search results proved to be trustworthy but it is tiresome. Online-services of website analysis will help you to perform this task and they may even provide you with important data on your rivals. For instance there is a free online service - cy-pr.com, which also shows the competitor-website of your website which is being analyzed. Its work is based on the number of inquiries which appear when website is shown in the search results.\r\n\r\nAs soon as you have defined your rivals, you can start analyzing their websites. There are different methods of website-analysis. The most widely used is the “horizontal” analysis of the website promotion via search results as it may help you see the rivals more obviously. SEO-analysis of websites of competing companies will help you to define why the particular sites appear on top of the search results and how to surpass them.\r\n\r\nNowadays there are many methods of SEO-analysis: some may be performed manually and some are automated. While performing SEO-analysis they take into consideration such parameters as its “trustworthy” reputation (Google PR), domain age, the number of indexed pages on the website, headlines, key words and page descriptions, density of key-words, etc.\r\n\r\nSo, competitors’ website analysis will help you to define the effective and ineffective methods of website promotion as well as to use the collected data for your own website promotion. Also, you will find out if you fully use your resources for website promotion and whether your budget is used correctly for the promoting purposes.\r\n<h3 data-fontsize=\"16\" data-lineheight=\"24\"><strong>We are traffic generation experts </strong></h3>\r\nWiseSwans SEO Services has a proven track record of search engine domination. Find out how our SEO San Diego can take you to the top of Google.\r\n<div id=\"spr_container\"></div>','What is the use of competitors’ website analysis?','','publish','closed','closed','','use-competitors-website-analysis','','','2025-10-20 10:11:32','2025-10-20 07:11:32','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/use-competitors-website-analysis/',0,'post','',0),(1870,3,'2016-12-31 06:27:43','2016-12-31 06:27:43','Backlinks (incoming links, inbound links or external links) are links that are redirecting user to the site from another websites. Before the introduction of search engines, they were used as a tool of web navigation. Practically, these links still play a key role in the site promotion today, so their checking description is a very important.\r\n\r\nWebsite’s promotion efficiency in search engines highly depends on the quality (from what kind of sites user can be redirected) and the number of backlinks. This factor remains significant in spite of the case that leading players in the search engine market, such as Google and Yahoo, permanently reduce its importance in the search results.\r\n\r\nTo analyze the efficiency of the promotion or to perform in-time measures to address bad quality links or deleting already paid links, it is very useful to know origin sites of incoming links. It will help to perform the analysis in general as well as in specific methods. That can be done by using various tools provided by search engines – Google Webmaster Tools, for instance.\r\n\r\nHow to check backlinks with Google Webmaster Tool?\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>On the Webmaster Tools homepage choose the site for analysis;</li>\r\n 	<li>Then enter the tool panel, select Search Traffic;</li>\r\n 	<li>In the popup menu click on Links to Your Site.</li>\r\n 	<li>After that, you will able to see the following data: number of domains that have links to the site and the number of links in each domain. Click on the specified domain to see details.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDo not have an account in Webmaster Tool? Need to check backlinks on another sites (belonging to competitors, for example) to evaluate they? Probably, the most popular online service for site exploring and link checking is Ahrefs (ahrefs.com).\r\n\r\nThis service is chargeable. However, some functions are available for free (of course, with some limitations). Every visitor can check inbound links for one website once a day. To do it, type the desired URL in the field and then press Try It for Free. You will discover the number of backlinks, referred sites, links classes (dofollow/nofollow), links indexation (new and lost links) graph, the most popular link texts (also called anchors).\r\n\r\nThus, this service gives actual information and statistics regarding backlinks. According to Ahrefs’s restrictions for a free version, only five domains can be seen by unregistered users and maximum of ten are possible to see for registered users with free account. In a full (commercial) version of the service there are no such limitations.\r\n\r\nSo, it is very simple to check inbound links with these service tools. Nevertheless, it only the first stage. Then this data must be correctly evaluated to use it for optimization or for search engines promotion or to make complex competitors’ analysis. The recommended solution here is to involve the professional web-studio or web promo team into the process.\r\n<h3 data-fontsize=\"16\" data-lineheight=\"24\"><strong>We are traffic generation experts </strong></h3>\r\nWiseSwans SEO Services has a proven track record of search engine domination. Find out how our San Diego SEO can take you to the top of Google.\r\n<div id=\"spr_container\"></div>','How Backlinks Can Be Checked?','','publish','closed','closed','','backlinks-can-checked','','','2025-10-20 09:37:42','2025-10-20 06:37:42','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/backlinks-can-checked/',0,'post','',0),(1872,3,'2016-12-31 06:27:43','2016-12-31 06:27:43','<h2><span style=\"background: white;\">What are affiliate web sites from the point of view of searching promotion?</span></h2>\r\nIn the case company has a number of sites, which are promoted at the same of similar topical searching requests, certain searching system sanctions can be imposed on one, or more, of them for so called affiliating. As a result, sites which are recognized by searching systems as affiliate go down in ranks and lose visitors. It will be said further about the ways of recognizing <em>affiliate web sites</em> by the searching systems and what do with these web sites.\r\n\r\nThe searching systems are operating effectively to reach the growing of effectiveness of their algorism, thus the new improvements appear. They help to clean the searching results from web undergrade sites, or web sites which don`t answer the users questions. <em>The cleaners for affiliation</em> is exactly one of such improvement, they deal with the availability of web sites of the same company.\r\n\r\nIf there are links leading to the several web sites of the same company in the adjacent places, it would lower the objectiveness of the searching results, that`s why searching engines try to avoid such situations. For this <em>a special group of cleaners</em> exists, which work is aimed on removal from the results ‘odd’ web sites of the same company. These are the cleaners for affiliate, and the web sites under their control are called affiliate in practice exploratory movement.\r\n\r\nFirst of all, the web sites with <em>identic or alike</em> domain info, IP address, possessor’s info, textual and media content, styling, structure, etc. are at the ‘risk group’ for getting the sanctions for affiliation. Of course, the more such matches the higher is a chance of facing the cleaners which mentioned. In addition, if the web sites are progressing at the same or related searches, the risk is increasing.\r\n\r\nYou can find a plenty of cleaners in searching systems, but how can we find out if the site was sanctioned definitely for affiliating? Some receptions can be used to do it. One of them is <em>to check all company web sites</em> which are moved by the same searching. If it shows that one web site is on the same positions but the others are extremely lowered in ranks, it is likely that these sites became the affiliate for the searching system.\r\n\r\nThe second technique for checking if the site was cleanered for affiliation is a usage of а <em>particular searching request</em>. For Google, is: “keyword&lt;&lt;(url=\"domain1.com\"|url=\"domain2.com\")”. Here the domain1.com and domain2.com are the addresses of the company`s web sites. If the check shows only one of the mentioned web sites, the other one is recognized as affiliate.\r\n\r\nIf the web site <em>fell under the influence of the cleaners</em> for affiliation as well as of any other cleaners, it will be rather difficult to go through this problem: you will have to ‘separate’ similar web sites and then to call maintainer of searching engines in order to exclude authorizations. So, of course, it is much easier to eschew affiliation taking right decisions in developing each of companies’ web sites.\r\n\r\nThe searching systems are opposed to them because they cause occupation of all popular results by one company, what is unacceptable. If different web sites of the company don`t try to occupy the searching results (<em>are promoted by different keywords</em>, work toward solving of various problems and have no matches) there will be no sanctions imposed on them.\r\n<h3 data-fontsize=\"16\" data-lineheight=\"24\"><strong>We are traffic generation experts </strong></h3>\r\nWiseSwans SEO Services has a proven track record of search engine domination. Find out how our San Diego SEO can take you to the top of Google.\r\n<div id=\"spr_container\"></div>','What are affiliate web sites from the point of view of searching promotion?','','publish','closed','closed','','affiliate-web-sites-point-view-searching-promotion','','','2025-10-20 09:38:08','2025-10-20 06:38:08','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/affiliate-web-sites-point-view-searching-promotion/',0,'post','',0),(1874,3,'2016-12-31 06:27:43','2016-12-31 06:27:43','<h2><span style=\"background: white;\">How to determine the most effective inquiries for your site promotion?</span></h2>\r\nMany website possessors would like to adopt all possible words and expressions inquiries from their sites’ semantical nucleus to develop their websites in the search systems successfully. The matter is that they mistakenly consider this way is the most useful. As the matter of fact, <em>to promote the website</em> with all its inquiries will be much more expensive and a little bit time-consuming. The best variant is to choose the most important inquiries and pay heed for them. There are several recommendations for you to determine the appropriate keys.\r\n\r\nActually, the site development always takes certain expenses. According to this, if you <em>promote more inquiries simultaneously</em>, you will go to more expenses. At one time, your expenses can appear extremely high so they can`t be recouped at all. As a result, any progress of your site will lose its sense. Anyway, you should try to avoid this situation. Thus it is necessary to find out what keywords are the most suitable right now to pay the greatest heed to.\r\n\r\nIn order to <em>select the most suitable inquiries</em> (words and expressions) for development of your site, you`d better to compare the forcefulness of each word with the expenses, spent on promotion. In the case when this process takes quite a long period of time but doesn’t attract enough guests on the site, your campaign should do without this key.\r\n\r\nThe <em>affectivity of searching inquiries</em> can be determined in various schemes, although more often we can judge about it by the number of inquiries and clicks. It means that an inquiry can be considered more effective when it is frequently used by users. The <em>expenses spent on promotion</em> are determined in their turn by the precise information about competitiveness in ranks, current positions in search systems and about a promotion cost prime.\r\n\r\nAs a rule, the process of the estimation of the affectivity of expenses, spent on determination of inquiries, is done manually or with a help of the automatic services. For instance, <em>frequency of inquiries</em> is analyzed with a help of some online services. For example, Google ‘keyword planner’.\r\n\r\nSpeaking about the level of <em>competitiveness</em>, it can be analyzed only manually by registration of inquiries results. While doing it, you should pay great heed on: how many searching results there are; how many links on start pages are in the top 10 results; the frequency of inquiries in snippets; what is the average age of top 10 sites; are there any stable competitors in the top 10 result (as Wikipedia, YouTube, Amazon and so on).\r\n\r\nAfter all necessary analyzes and checking you can choose words which are the most suitable for developing. The ideal variant would be inquiries with<em> high forcefulness and little expenses</em>. Though, it is almost impossible to find such inquiries and as a result those ones with some equilibration between the affectivity and expenses which you have to go for them, because a inquiry by its own is already effective enough to attract new object visitors to the website, and at the same time it doesn`t require too much expenses.\r\n<h3 data-fontsize=\"16\" data-lineheight=\"24\"><strong>We are traffic generation experts </strong></h3>\r\nWiseSwans SEO Services has a proven track record of search engine domination. Find out how our SEO San Diego can take you to the top of Google.','How to determine the most effective inquiries for your site promotion?','','publish','closed','closed','','determine-effective-inquiries-site-promotion','','','2025-10-20 09:38:35','2025-10-20 06:38:35','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/determine-effective-inquiries-site-promotion/',0,'post','',0),(1876,3,'2016-12-31 06:27:43','2016-12-31 06:27:43','<h2><span style=\"background: white;\">Site Promotion in the Social Media</span></h2>\r\nThe main attention in the site promotion process in the social media must be paid to public groups and pages and the quality of their content. They are main points that help to draw the attention of new visitors and retain the existing subscribers. Normally, social media post must include graphic illustration to increase visitors’ perception. Nevertheless, there are some rules to make the post expressive and effective, which are the part of what is often called social media marketing (SMM).\r\n\r\nUntil recently, cute cat pictures (or other cute pictures – animals, children, nature or so on) were the universal key to success. Undoubtedly, cute cats are very popular and give lots of positive emotions for many people. Unfortunately, for serious business projects cute cats are useless, because in this case users pay too much attention to the picture and not to the author or other info. Thus, cute images will hardly increase sales, attract the target audience or make the brand famous. Thereby, here is the basic rule – to make an effective SMM campaign, it is important to use images that are relevant to the company’s goals.\r\n\r\nThe following advices will help to create actual and valuable content for the SMM campaign using pictures.\r\n\r\n<em>Image format</em>\r\n\r\nTry to find the balance between the parameters of the pictures (as high as possible) and requirements of the specific site (size, resolution and others).\r\n\r\nTake into account that some social media have built-in mechanisms to fit uploaded pictures to their limits. This usually leads to the resizing or reduction in the image quality for the pictures that are too large. So, it is advised to manually edit the materials before posting to minimize the negative effect of an automatic fitting.\r\n\r\n<em>Pictures are connected with posts</em>\r\n\r\nImages should be not only relevant to company’s goals, but also connected with the specific posts. There are some methods to express the post’s content correctly:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Before/after photo.</li>\r\n 	<li>Product use in real life.</li>\r\n 	<li>Graphs and charts (if there are many important numbers in the post).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe source of images is a matter too. The best way is to use your own and unique illustrations which are always something new to the eye. If it is not possible, try to purchase photos from photo banks or public domains, but do not forget about copyright restrictions.\r\n\r\n<em>Try not to use conventional pictures</em>\r\n\r\nNew and unique images are vital for the effective SMM campaign. Conventional photos have been reposted many times before and visitors will get tired of them. Use original and unconventional materials to promote the post successfully.\r\n\r\nStatistics prove the popularity of illustrated posts. Properly chosen picture definitely raises the overall rating of the post.\r\n\r\nHowever, keep in mind that SMM activities demand the complex approach. It includes not only creating new posts, but also use different ways of promotion, communication with subscribers and various measures to maintain the company’s reputation in the social media.\r\n<h3 data-fontsize=\"16\" data-lineheight=\"24\"><strong>We are traffic generation experts </strong></h3>\r\nWiseSwans SEO Services has a proven track record of search engine domination. Find out how our San Diego SEO can take you to the top of Google.','Site Promotion in the Social Media: How to Illustrate Posts Correctly','','publish','closed','closed','','site-promotion-social-media-illustrate-posts-correctly','','','2025-10-20 09:36:48','202