n the search engine listings. This in turn, would encourage more visitors to the sites and naturally boost up the sales.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rules of adding new content</strong>\r\n\r\nWhen new content is being added to the website, it is very important to keep note of the fact that should be in context with the given topic and should not feel out of place. Next most important thing is to categorize the new content appropriately. One of the best practices is to keep upgrading the content of the site with client and customer feedback, product and service reviews and press releases. The more often content in a website is replaced with fresh and better quality content, the better are its chances of showing up amongst the first few results in the search engine listings.\r\n\r\n<strong>Importance of keywords</strong>\r\n\r\nNo matter what the content of each page of a website, it is always a better idea to furnish the on-page titles as well as the title of the webpage with high demand keywords or key phrase. Besides this, the short descriptions or summaries in the pages that depict the whole theme of the content must also be furnished with keywords and key phrases.','Fresh Content How Does it help in Search Engine Optimization?','','publish','closed','closed','','fresh-content-help-search-engine-optimization','','','2025-10-20 09:23:06','2025-10-20 06:23:06','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/fresh-content-help-search-engine-optimization/',0,'post','',0),(1916,3,'2016-12-31 06:28:12','2016-12-31 06:28:12','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nProving the value of <a href=\"http://rightonit1/\">Search Engine Optimization</a> has become almost an obsession with most companies. So here are a few statistics that can help prove a point, either in favour or against an SEO investment. Also, experts now realise that convincing C-level executives to think of any SEO investment at all entails bandying about a few stats and figures because at the end of the day, it’s all a number game. So here they are:\r\n\r\nOf all the SEO campaigns, evidence has it that almost 40 percent of them have healthy returns of around 500 percent. In contrast, only 22 percent of Pay-Per-Click campaigns boast of success\r\nAlmost 62 percent users click on links available on the first page itself\r\nWhen a search is unsuccessful, 80 percent of users refine their keywords to search again\r\nNow if these stats don’t sway things in your favour then read on to discover the other things you can do to prove the value of SEO.\r\n\r\n<strong>Select the right time frame to measure SEO returns:</strong>\r\n\r\nIt’s smart to take seasonality into account. Depending on how frequently budgeting decisions are made think of a Year Over Year, monthly or quarterly time frame. Another approach to selecting the right framework is to think on the lines of Key Sales Periods. For instance, the hotel industry experiences spikes in enquiries at the weekends and during holidays and vacations. It’s easier to show the correlation between an increase in SEO activities and sales during such peak times. Then apply the following commonly used formula- Revenue- Investment/Investment multiplied by 100\r\n\r\n<strong>Be smart about customer profiling:</strong>\r\n\r\nAggregate data reveals nothing! Even organic keyword reports provide sketchy insights. What really works is segmentation or customer profiling for not all companies are interested in customer outside their region or country. Also not all companies benefit from customers who land on a blog and then move to the product page. Segments that are most useful in terms of calculating ROI include users who’ve filled up forms or made it to the checkout stage, geographic segments or visits to certain sections or your website.\r\nThere is enough to show that <a href=\"http://rightonit1/seo-and-organic-search-ranking/\">SEO</a> has value, and value that is immense. While it does not take very much to employ SEO to almost every business, it is only when the benefits start to show that you know just what you have gifted yourself. These measures alone can help prove the value of SEO to those who still remain skeptical about taking the plunge!','Proving the value of SEO','','publish','closed','closed','','proving-value-seo','','','2025-10-20 09:24:14','2025-10-20 06:24:14','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/proving-value-seo/',0,'post','',0),(1918,3,'2016-12-31 06:28:12','2016-12-31 06:28:12','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAre you one of those already discouraged having sat hours online without being able to sell a thing? Well, this article comes loaded with the most effective marketing schemes and techniques that will increase your chances of online Marketing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Driving traffic</strong>\r\nGenerating traffic is one of the primary goals of <a href=\"http://rightonit1/\">internet marketing</a>. Often, it happens so that a company has some of the best products and services on offer. However, owing to poor marketing, they are hardly noticed and thus, in no time, it perishes. Once a company has been able to build that trust and a stronger relationship with the clients and customers from the niche market, it starts gaining ground and its sales figures start picking up from there.\r\n\r\n<strong>Back Linking</strong>\r\n\r\nThe more the number of links a website has, the better are its chances of ranking higher in the search engines. Both quality and quantity matter in case of back linking. Leaving back links to your website in your comments to relevant and popular blog sites, has a great potential to draw visitors to the site. Thus, this way a company can build both link power as well as generate more traffic.\r\n\r\n<strong>Marketing via blogs</strong>\r\n\r\nOne of the keys of internet marketing success lies with better blogging. After all, a blog site is a place where readers get the first hand information on the product or services or about the business and all that is being promoted by the business. The readers get to ask questions