rvices”. This means that you should target local audiences if you are doing business with local buyers and clients.\r\n\r\nIt is essential to note that Google has been doing constant updates to its search algorithms, and thus, you should always keep abreast on the latest updates Google has made to its algorithm and how such updates would impact the <a href=\"http://rightonit1/seo-and-organic-search-ranking/\">SEO strategies</a> that you’re currently implementing for your small business. SEO for small businesses are not rocket science and it is highly possible for someone with no SEO background to perfect it in matter of months. It is an incredibly essential skill to pick up as business owners and that skill alone could just possibly be the missing puzzle in perfecting your marketing funnel.','Understanding SEO for Small Businesses','','publish','closed','closed','','understanding-seo-small-businesses','','','2025-10-20 09:29:44','2025-10-20 06:29:44','',0,'http://www.wiseswans.com/2016/12/31/understanding-seo-small-businesses/',0,'post','',0),(1931,3,'2016-12-31 06:28:12','2016-12-31 06:28:12','It’s a well-known fact that competitions for offline businesses are generally fierce, particularly if you’re based in San Diego.\r\n\r\nTherefore, many business owners located in San Diego are currently looking to tap into the online market to boost their revenues. If you are one of them, and are currently looking for customized SEO service providers in San Diego that aims to work on your business goals and standards, then this article would be of interests to you.\r\n\r\nUndoubtedly, you’d want to engage a team of experts who could deliver great services based on the prevailing market costs to optimize your website. Whether you are into small or big Internet marketing businesses, you would want to bring adequate amount of traffic to your website in order to attract more clients. Of course, your goal does not stop on page views but on how you can actually make each client vis