ncy requests will allow using several keyword phrases on one page without risk of the page being too long.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Characterized by higher accuracy.</strong>\r\nSuch requests consist of several words and allow offering to the visitor the particular product or service for which the visitor is searching. For example, with “coach” request the visitor will get to the root catalogue and will be searching for the needed product, but the at the same time the request “red leather coach” will get him to the needed page in a few seconds.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>No need to frequently repeat the request on the page.</strong>\r\nSince the request is highly accurate there is no need to repeat in many times in the text. Consequently the text becomes more readable, and in addition it can be optimized simultaneously for several requests.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis opens a perfect opportunity to optimize the web pages in several directions and at the same time to keep the reasonable volumes of text content. This is particularly true for e-commerce stores with big assortment. For example, you can easily place on one page three low-frequency requests “red leather coach”, “black leather coach” and “white leather coach”, while high frequency request as “coach”, “bed” and “sofa” on the same page absolutely inappropriate.\r\nIn other words the <em>website marketing</em> in several directions is way more effective with low frequency requests rather than using widespread high-frequency requests. And it will give additional opportunities for optimization for certain regions of the country, which is a crucial advantage of this type of optimization. This special feature together with considerably lower price of low-frequency <strong>SEO marketing</strong> makes this type of optimization very attractive for small local companies that only start developing their website.\r\nModern  Internet <span style=\"background-color: #f5f6f5;\">business </span>or just business representation online ca